This paper deals with object localization in images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed method involves joint analysis of all windows in the image, taking into account their similarity in appearance space as well as their spatial relations in the image plane. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for optimizing the score function over all candidate windows in an image, which involves learning its parameters using structured output regression. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with image processing and analysis, which suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
